          }
        },
        "text_LHGLnM": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Metatarsalgia is a general term used to denote a painful foot condition in the metatarsal region of the foot (the area just before the toes, more commonly referred to as the ball-of-the-foot). This is a common foot disorder that can affect the bones and joints at the ball-of-the-foot. Metatarsalgia (ball-of-foot-pain) is often located under the 2nd, 3rd, and 4th metatarsal heads, or more isolated at the first metatarsal head (near the big toe).</p>",
            "text_font": "body",
            "text_size": "subtext-md",
            "text_max_size": 32,
            "text_line_height": 1.6,
            "text_letter_spacing": 0,
